Text.Value: I... I was wrong. I gotta release them.
We're marching to Moonrise. And no death-curse'll be stopping us.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.logicalname: at least one other loyalist still alive

Text.Value: It's a tough journey. The gnomes will be a burden.
That death-curse be damned, I'm heading to Moonrise.
*The mark glows, but you feel nothing in response. Your illithid power is beyond reach until you rest.*
You mentioned a death-curse. Is the journey so dangerous?
*Your mind lurches, reeling suddenly as if... bitten.*
*Something stirs deep within you, hungry and alert... it's taking something you'll never get back.*
Slaves could slow us down - if they survive the curse at all.
Enter his mind. 'Release the gnomes.'
*His mind is closed to you.*
Draw on the power within to enforce your will.
We're not letting that happen, are we?
Read the duergar's mind.
Whatever's wrong with you, I hope it's not contagious.
*The presence deep in your mind is awake, unblinking. This is it. A single word pervades your consciousness: 'Soon'.*
The gnomes should be able to go where they please. They are not the duergar's to keep.
*Your mind is full, bursting with ecstasy and terror. Finally, it is coming. You are becoming.*
Attack the duergar.
The surface is dangerous. I'm not so sure it's safe to travel.

EditorData.logicalname: Player got surface warning at elevator

Text.Value: Draw on the power within to enforce your will.
Let. Them. Go.
The gnomes are free. Now walk away, while I'm feeling generous.
Listen up, bastards - I'm taking charge. Clean your 'nads and pack up.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.logicalname: at least one other loyalist still alive

Text.Value: What about the gnomes? What happens to them?

EditorData.logicalname: At least one gnome still alive

Text.Value: Your heart made of stone? They deserved freedom - and you denied it.
Time for the General to recognise us duergar that have been toiling 'round here.
It's time I cut you down once and for all.
This General sounds powerful. Who is he, exactly?
Gnomes - it's your lucky day. Get your squat arses moving, before I take a brand to them.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general

Text.Value: Shit - True Soul Nere's nothing but grub-chow now.
Enter his mind. 'Release the gnomes.'
Ask and receive. Zavagh!

EditorData.NodeContext: za-VAHG. A battle cry leading to combat

Text.Value: Speak up. You can't just let the clan keep them.
*A strange symbol glows, marked on their flesh, and something within you stirs in response.*

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Delete if you are talking to a companion.

Text.Value: That head of yours must be mixed up. The slaves are for the General. End of.
Shit - suppose you're right. No use hauling dead weight.
That curse chokes the air from here clear to Moonrise. Not that I'm worried.
Let's do this!
What the... you messing with my mind? I won't stand for it!
Smug words for a walking corpse. Zavagh!

EditorData.NodeContext: za-VAHG. A battle cry leading to combat

Text.Value: *As the symbol glows, power courses through you. Authority.*
Leave.
They will make a fine offering.
Come and take them, then!
*A shadow swims across your vision, and a familiar voice tells you to be calm. You are loved.*
Absolute let Nere and Thrinn both get capped. She's not offin' me now.
*A shiver runs across your mind... You feel sated.*
What - you'd think I'd just toss 'em? They're coming with me. A gift for the General.
Then show me. And may the Absolute bless the victor!
Brittle are the foundations upon which the houses of tyrants are built. It seems I judged you to be less brittle than you really are.
*You focus on the source of the power, but it is quiet and still. It needs to rest.*
*Your blood runs quicker, feeding the gnawing absence at the centre of your mind.*
Hells yes. The General can't ignore a haul of fresh slaves.
I am freeing these gnomes. Just try and stop me.
Yeah? Well I won't give you lip - what the Absolute wants, She gets.
He's the Absolute's Chosen, the way Nere talked. Building an army at Moonrise - best of the best.
She'll part the curse for me. I got complete faith.
Fine. Not looking to piss off a True Soul.
Now I'm in charge here, he'll make me a True Soul. Maybe even a Disciple.

Synopsis: Player has sided with Nere, but Nere and Thrinn are dead by the time combat is over. In that case, a duergar initiates dialogue and tells you his plans and you get to decide the gnomes' fate.
